bug.author: cchadowitz-pf
bug.summary: Caffe model service crashes with free(): invalid pointer when using "best" larger than available labels
bug.description:
When using a "best" value larger than the number of labels the caffe model was trained for, the server crashes with the error below. Using "best": -1 is fine, but in my example, the model only has 2 possible labels and crashes when using "best": 5. The docker image I'm using may be a bit out of date, it is the jolibrain/deepdetect_cpu:ci-master tag with digest 6a36e4e0d2bd10479f1868a9636406c51fa0c68e74d4d54d91586c0fc2a5289f. The model I'm using is the nsfw model, I can upload the various files for it if necessary.
